{
  "texts": [
    "In principle, node-permutation invariance would follow automatically once a target algorithm is correctly implemented; on the other hand, as capacity and data grow, variability across relabelings may already shrink before that.",
    "We note that, absent potential positional spillage in (ℓ, S) and strong positional biases, node relabelings do not change the computational workload presented to the model, in terms of its algorithmic execution (also see next paragraph).Edge encoding gathers the data structure and its inner edge ordering rule.",
    "The former determines how the relational structure is described, the latter how this is presented as a sequence.",
    "Prominent choices for the data structure would be edge-list, adjacency-list or adjacency-matrix (see App.",
    "Example Prompts)."
  ]
}